Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.35,0:00:24.30,Default,op,0,0,0,,Under the skies that are still unknown to me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.30,0:00:28.37,Default,op,0,0,0,,I know, you're doing just the same -
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.37,0:00:29.94,Default,op,0,0,0,,Dreaming
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.94,0:00:35.21,Default,op,0,0,0,,Just a small glow\NFrom those great days
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.21,0:00:38.08,Default,op,0,0,0,,Is what dragging you along
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.08,0:00:41.87,Default,op,0,0,0,,Giving you faith and some comfort
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.87,0:00:45.76,Default,op,0,0,0,,Under the sun that scorches badly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.00,0:00:52.13,Default,op,0,0,0,,I only want to see your guise
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.13,0:00:53.91,Default,op,0,0,0,,But instead...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.91,0:00:59.14,Default,op,0,0,0,,I only watch \NWith tears on my face
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.14,0:01:04.74,Default,op,0,0,0,,As you slowly disappear in this noon haze
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.74,0:01:07.76,Default,op,0,0,0,,We're alone \NWe're alone
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.76,0:01:11.31,Default,op,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1000)}Walking this world on our own
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.36,0:01:16.53,Default,op,0,0,0,,{\fade(1000,0)}Looking for each other since long ago
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.53,0:01:22.46,Default,op,0,0,0,,In the end, in the end, \NAfter the day we finally meet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.46,0:01:26.97,Default,op,0,0,0,,{\b1\bord1\blur1\t(2100,2200,\shad3\blur3\c&HABADD8&)}We won't ever have to say "Goodbye"
Comment: 0,0:01:33.06,0:01:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{OP END}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.60,0:01:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Queen's Cup 90 finals \Nwere postponed due to the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.10,0:01:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jean Ryder vs Oka Hiromi match\Nwas rescheduled to 1 pm of the following day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.78,0:02:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.59,0:02:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Your room was empty, \Nso headed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.83,0:02:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like a cafe au lait.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.89,0:02:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.10,0:02:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday evening, \NI've been to Madame Butterfly's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.50,0:02:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if I should confide it to you \Nuntil Hiromi's finals are over,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.80,0:02:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but it seems Madame Butterfly is retiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.07,0:02:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Your cafe au lait.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.05,0:02:51.93,Default,,0,0,280,,{\bord4\blur15\3c&HAC907F&\t(0,1100,\bord0\blur0.55)\c&HFEFEFD&\fnGabriola\fs48\frz360\3a&H2D&\fscx162\fscy137}Episode 12
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.00,0:02:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.68,0:03:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My match is at 1 pm tomorrow \Nand waiting in the hotel is no fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.68,0:03:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have plenty of time to make it there tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.67,0:03:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.22,0:03:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.82,0:03:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't sleep this night in my own bed, \NI won't get any sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.46,0:03:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I also missed mom's cooking!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.89,0:03:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.69,0:03:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just 4 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.83,0:03:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You did well, all the way to the finals.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.83,0:03:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I recorded every TV broadcast of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.82,0:03:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.53,0:03:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A salmon pot will do just well! How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.80,0:03:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.57,0:03:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take a little walk outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.31,0:03:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is salmon pot okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.11,0:03:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.09,0:03:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Katsura.\NCan I speak to Ms. Oka?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.16,0:03:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Hiromi leave the hotel \Nwithout Mr. Katsura's permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.70,0:03:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm... Making sure she made it there. \NThat's all I needed to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.57,0:04:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for the inconvenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.71,0:04:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika, Oka's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.05,0:04:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.32,0:04:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka came to see you, \Nwaiting in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.19,0:04:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish her the best of luck in tomorrow's finals. \NPlease tell her so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.63,0:04:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry, Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.77,0:04:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika is taking a little nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.41,0:04:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,She deserves some rest now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka! Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.69,0:04:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.00,0:04:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Todo...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.43,0:04:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Todo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.68,0:05:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, I went to the venue \Nbut today's match was postponed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.00,0:05:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't in the hotel,\Nso I headed to your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.41,0:05:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly retires?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.24,0:05:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it confirmed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.34,0:05:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to her to confirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.38,0:05:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But then she didn't wish to meet me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.58,0:05:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, last night, \Nwhen Midorikawa managed to see her,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.80,0:05:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as she was sitting there, \Nexhausted and in tears:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.62,0:05:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"Forgive me. \NI cannot play tennis anymore."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.26,0:05:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,To all inquiries of Chairman Ryuzaki, her father, \Nshe just hung her head in sorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.43,0:05:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It troubles me so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.00,0:05:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It is all so wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.87,0:05:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With this on my mind, \NI cannot play tennis...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.54,0:05:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I was aspiring to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I could only climb this far \Nbecause I thought Madame Butterfly is waiting here. {I could only carry on climbing because I thought Madame Butterfly is waiting up there.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.74,0:05:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what happens in finals tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.08,0:05:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If Madame Butterfly quits tennis, \Nit ends for me as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.65,0:06:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember us sitting in this restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.51,0:06:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like today, \Nit was pouring rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.59,0:06:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I either become a pro or quit tennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.36,0:06:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was completely lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.30,0:06:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, while drinking that burning-hot coffee \Nhere with you, I could make up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.80,0:06:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"I will try my best no matter what."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.71,0:06:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This restaurant, which is nothing but commonplace, \Nbecame a starting point for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.06,0:06:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That was how I thought of it then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.51,0:06:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if I fail,\NI won't lose my spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.45,0:06:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just come to this restaurant once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.07,0:06:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, that day it won't rain anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.32,0:06:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also no telling if you'll come here with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.20,0:06:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Chances are, this whole restaurant \Nwon't be present by that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.08,0:06:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm fine with that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.00,0:06:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sitting here with you, it was raining, \Nthe coffee was burning-hot - that's the only truth for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.54,0:06:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That was when I mustered the courage to go forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.01,0:07:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A wonderful decision, it seemed to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.58,0:07:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because... Because I knew \Nthat even if I fail, I won't lose everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.16,0:07:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and that if I come here, \Nyou will equip me with courage once again, surely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.43,0:07:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder where Madame Butterfly's restaurant is, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.93,0:07:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1000)}Right now she is desperately trying to recall this place.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:22.81,0:07:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(1000,0)}All alone, certain that at such a moment, \Nnot a soul would show up at her special place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.58,0:07:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Once Madame Butterfly returns there, \Nshe'll need time to think it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.88,0:07:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll come back to the light, surely. {She will certainly go out to everyone again.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.82,0:07:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, Oka, we have to just wait patiently. \NUnfortunately, there's nothing else we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.38,0:08:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.72,0:08:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You dumped away my training plan just to come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.37,0:08:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Fortunate of you, Todo! \NWithout rain postponement, you'd never see the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.37,0:08:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.63,0:08:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Remind me to teach you some pro responsibility!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.02,0:08:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.97,0:08:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Get on the court.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.14,0:08:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go, Hiromi. \NOkay? The time has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.64,0:08:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one more push, Oka.\NThere's no retreating from the final round.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.72,0:08:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about Madame B until the match's conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.25,0:08:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.62,0:08:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who kept winning and could advance into the final stage \Nare obliged to fight for those who got eliminated along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.18,0:08:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa, Broir, Morita, Ling, and of course Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.00,0:09:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who lost remain on the court, \Nrepresented by your fierce fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.77,0:09:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean to say you forgot them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.84,0:09:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I remember them all, still lucidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.64,0:09:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand up then!\NStand on the court!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.64,0:09:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And show everyone your ultimate fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.82,0:09:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(600,0)}Reika!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.71,0:09:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We should leave shortly for the Colosseum.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.38,0:09:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ready to go out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.85,0:09:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.69,0:09:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Today I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.22,0:09:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Rightly so. \NThat's even better!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.63,0:10:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever was there, it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.93,0:10:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, you are not going to Colosseum?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.20,0:10:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears today I'm staying indoors as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.21,0:10:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But you cannot do that! \NYou are the Association Chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.81,0:10:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a major task of awarding the Cup to the champion!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.48,0:10:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone can replace me in this role.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.13,0:10:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.53,0:11:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But today, on such an important day, \Nnobody can replace me as your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.54,0:11:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are staying indoors for an entire day, \NI think I should too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.46,0:11:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can do anything for you, I must do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.00,0:11:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how it should be and how I want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.60,0:11:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.70,0:11:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi might very well become the champion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.84,0:11:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the only one \Nwho can award the Champion Cup to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.61,0:11:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you not looked forward to that day since long ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.28,0:11:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you always say that the Japanese Tennis Association \Nplaces its hopes in Oka?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.62,0:11:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And when that dream is about to be fulfilled, you turn away?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.50,0:11:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,From Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.07,0:11:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I tell you just one thing, Reika?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.81,0:11:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.87,0:11:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This defeat was essential for you, Reika.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.64,0:11:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to it, you can now move on and grow, \Nbreak the chains!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.92,0:12:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you forgive me for what I'm to say \Nbecause I see it appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.43,0:12:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.07,0:12:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us go, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.80,0:12:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the Colosseum together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.24,0:12:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's fine if you want to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.17,0:12:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I should go. I want to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.78,0:12:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.11,0:12:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi is doing her best, so I must see it. \NI want... I want to see it with my own eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.97,0:12:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Daigo...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.90,0:12:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I got you, Munakata.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.40,0:12:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Daigo, do it for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.01,0:12:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I got you, Munakata.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.74,0:13:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I got you perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.33,0:13:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust me to make it all OK, Munakata.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.49,0:13:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka keeps her service-game.{sounds controversial but there's no other way around} The score is tied. \NFrom the very first set, her offense is fierce!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.14,0:13:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A gain again!\NOka's return ace!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.57,0:13:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Since when did Oka \Nlearn to hit such a ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.19,0:13:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Jean Ryder, #7 in world rankings, \Nis much paler in the face now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.70,0:13:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.51,0:13:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.95,0:13:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Tea!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.48,0:13:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.14,0:13:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryder approaches the net!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.30,0:13:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.36,0:13:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,She hits!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.66,0:13:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Daigo, human beings touch and communicate \Nin a variety of different forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.50,0:13:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Through a variety of different approaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.67,0:14:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I once met Oka through the tennis approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.74,0:14:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether Oka likes it or not, there's no escaping the major premise{/ condition} \Nof me being the coach and Oka being the player.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.81,0:14:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I am responsible for sacrificing \Nher entire priceless youth to a greater cause of tennis. {/ That's why I am now responsible for sucking dry her entire priceless youth in order to replace it with tennis.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.92,0:14:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I got what you mean, Munakata.\NI got it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.57,0:14:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, the limit of tennis... \NThe limit to which I can teach her tennis is already near.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.39,0:14:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean to be a true player...\NWhat does it mean to be a true coach?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.46,0:14:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.35,0:14:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.52,0:14:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Goddamn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.44,0:14:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What a hot temper.\NIs that even worth of world's #7?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.53,0:15:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Unknown Oka Hiromi turned out formidable. \NIt's a shock for her!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.64,0:15:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Todo, that would suffice for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.81,0:15:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly,\Nthank you so much for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.88,0:15:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Katsura,\Ntoday, I'm not fighting here alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.09,0:15:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I was never fighting here alone, and I see it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.76,0:15:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd never manage to make it this far doing my best alone. \NI realized it suddenly while hitting the ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.25,0:15:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All this time I have been the most ordinary child. \NAn ordinary child, who happened to be playing this big match.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.14,0:15:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable, isn't it?\NI don't believe it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.48,0:15:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I know for sure is, it were Coach Katsura \Nand Madame Butterfly, Todo and Maki, Chairman Ryuzaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.48,0:15:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Chiba and Ozaki, and finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.67,0:15:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, Coach Munakata.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.65,0:16:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's thanks to all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.02,0:16:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what I truly believe right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.49,0:16:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Next one is tie-break!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.51,0:16:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Under a twelve-point system, \Nthe first player to score 7 points wins this set!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.75,0:16:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done, Oka! You scored 7 points! \NThe first set is rightfully yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.43,0:17:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,One more set. If Oka's sustains this vigor for just one more set, \Nher premier Queen Title will no longer a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.45,0:17:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Go for it, Oka! Till the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.96,0:17:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to hit those balls like Hiromi does it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.70,0:17:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.47,0:17:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{40-0.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.44,0:17:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,3 against 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.92,0:17:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.45,0:17:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a match point!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.87,0:17:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka is currently just one point away from victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.89,0:17:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryder has no room for a fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.24,0:17:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Half a step onward more!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.32,0:18:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Champion - Oka Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.78,0:18:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but did you want to show something \Nto me and Oka?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.50,0:19:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And this...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.34,0:19:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,On his last day, or maybe a day or two before that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.12,0:19:10.14,Default,,0,0,10,,{\an8\b0\fnVerdana}Munakata Jin
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.12,0:19:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,he wrote me this, his final letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.28,0:19:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and read. \NI wanted to show it to you for its contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.95,0:19:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Daigo. Still, teaching her tennis... \NThe limit to which I can teach her tennis is already closing in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.41,0:19:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a true player, to be a true coach, what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.00,0:19:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I spend the little time I have left, pondering.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.70,0:19:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What will Oka need when she eventually becomes stronger, \Nmastering everything she will ever need for her tennis?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.24,0:19:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, it won't be neither me, nor you, Daigo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.54,0:19:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because we ourselves \Nare walking just a bit ahead of Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.81,0:19:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, what Oka will really need by then
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.28,0:19:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is a mate who could share her walk{/ road}, \Nworries, grief and finally, joy, in the equal parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.09,0:20:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To whom she could bestow not just tennis, but everything else \Nas well... Faith. Whom she could put her faith in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.63,0:20:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, that person would be Oka's true coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.10,0:20:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Daigo, I entrust Oka to your command.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.45,0:20:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the time comes for you to pass this baton to another, \NI also want you to pick a person whom you can entrust her to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.14,0:20:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Because for someone as incapable{/ unfitting / inept} as me, \NOka is too amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.85,0:20:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Todo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.65,0:20:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.35,0:20:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In a year... No, even in half a year, after Oka completes \Nher transition to pro, her path will become even more rugged.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.46,0:20:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you be ready by then \Nto accept this baton from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.13,0:20:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot know what lies ahead, but until then, I will make every effort to become a person capable enough to accept it.{/ capable of accepting it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.11,0:20:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need any send-offs, you know. \NI'm not a child anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.48,0:20:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If I need you while you travel through America again, \Nhow do I contact you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.89,0:21:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be paying you a call each time my address changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.82,0:21:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's fine by me then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.76,0:21:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you ask, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.41,0:21:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking, \Nmaybe I should go to America too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.63,0:21:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll have more luck \Ngetting a Pro Qualification there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.50,0:21:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.94,0:21:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Great! Definitely! That's a great idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.14,0:21:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm starting over.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.61,0:21:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't hear you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.45,0:21:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.35,0:21:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.66,0:21:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, to celebrate your triumph, \NI want to give you some kind of present.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.63,0:21:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell me what you'd like?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.83,0:21:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I can not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.96,0:21:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.20,0:21:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because now I have everything I would ever want.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.84,0:21:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.47,0:22:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,15-0!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.05,0:22:09.47,Default,,0,66,20,,{\fade(400,0)\an3\fs35\blur1\bord0\b1}The end
Comment: 0,0:22:10.29,0:22:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{ED START}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.06,0:22:21.81,Default,ed,0,0,0,,There is one song I cannot ever forget
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.81,0:22:27.44,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Still, there's a face I'm willing to forget
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.44,0:22:30.40,Default,ed,0,0,0,,With her feelings messed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.40,0:22:33.28,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Alice got completely lost
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.28,0:22:38.47,Default,ed,0,0,0,,The midst of summer \NBrought her into one tricky love maze
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.79,0:22:45.38,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I want you to hug tightly\NAnd never let go of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.38,0:22:50.76,Default,ed,0,0,0,,One scared and timid tiny girl
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.76,0:22:57.64,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I quite remember our very first kiss \NAnd the beginning of all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.22,0:23:04.06,Default,ed,0,0,0,,While birds were singing for us...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.13,0:23:13.25,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I'll take a car and take a lonely trip
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.25,0:23:18.45,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I know it'll bring me \NTo the seashore
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.45,0:23:21.50,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Where only the the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.50,0:23:24.54,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Dazzlingly bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.54,0:23:30.07,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Could witness my long-awaited happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.47,0:23:32.57,Default,,0,0,110,,{\bord0\blur1\b1\an2\fs20}Thank you for watching. \NI was happy to translate and compile this release for you. \NYours truly, Perevodildo.
